Lay a @British chicken breasts{4} on the #chopping board{}, place your hand flat on top and slice it all the way through from the side, so that there are two thin halves. Repeat for the other chicken breasts. Now slice each half into thin strips and then cut the strips into small 1cm cubes.

> Tip: Slicing the chicken in half first means you will be able to cut very small pieces of chicken.

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. On a separate chopping board, cut the @onion{1} in half through the root, peel and chop into roughly ½cm pieces. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Grate the @lime{1} zest on the fine side of the #grater{}.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and your onion. Cook for ~{5%minutes} until your onion is soft (don't worry if it's slightly browned), then add your chicken to the pan. Sprinkle in your lime zest, @Mexican spice{1.5}, a @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{good grind} and cook for ~{6-7%minutes} until your chicken is slightly browned and cooked through.

> Tip: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once your onion and chicken are cooked, put them in a large #bowl{} and add the @baby spinach{1}. Stir into your chicken mixture (your spinach should wilt slightly) then add your cheddar cheese and @sour cream{1}. Mix together so everything is combined.

Line a large #baking tray{} with baking paper (or tinfoil if you don't have any baking paper). Put a @corn tortilla{8} on your chopping board and arrange a couple of spoonfuls of your chicken mixture down the centre of the tortilla leaving 1cm empty at each end. Fold the two gaps at the ends of the line of chicken mixture into the centre, then fold the wrap over so you have an enclosed parcel. Repeat with the other tortillas... your taquitos are ready!

Put each of your taquitos onto the baking tray, seam side down. Drizzle a little @oil{little} over them, then pop on the top shelf of your oven to cook for ~{10-15%minutes} or until slightly browned (but not burnt!).

In the meantime, chop the @vine tomatoes{2} into roughly 1cm pieces. Remove the root from the @baby gem lettuce{2} and cut into 1cm wide slices. Squeeze half the lime juice into a large bowl and pour in ½ @olive oil{1%tbsp} per person. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch}, a good grind of @black pepper{good grind} and a good pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have some). Mix together with a #fork{}, then add your tomatoes and lettuce to the bowl and mix together with your hands to give everything a good coating. Taste, and add more lime juice if you like things zesty!

When your taquitos are ready, remove them from your oven and serve two per person with your salad on the side. Enjoy!